    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"managing\" it just feels like a lie they tell so they don't have to face the reality. even if the meds work a little, the underlying thing is still there. it's just a slow, agonizing decline. honestly, sometimes i look at it and think it would be more merciful to just... have everything be still. than to keep dragging this through years of more pain. does that even make sense? to just want the noise and the hurting to stop for good?",
